<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="86" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,651,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Distribution, habitat and phenology:—</emphasis>
This species is known only from Seasonally Dry Tropical Forests within Caatinga vegetation in the southern portion of 
<emphasis box="[661,905,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
Chapada 
<taxonomicName box="[771,905,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Diamantina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Diamantina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[919,1051,194,220]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Bahia State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1134,194,220]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The region surrounding the municipality of Rio de Contas is a known center of diversity within the 
<emphasis box="[930,1173,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
Chapada 
<taxonomicName box="[1039,1173,231,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Diamantina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Diamantina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and holds large numbers of endemic flowering plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Harley, R. M." box="[479,624,266,293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" refId="ref3090" refString="Harley, R. M. (1995) Introduction. In: Stannard, B. L. (Ed.) Flora of the Pico das Almas, Chapada Diamantina, Bahia, Brasil. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." type="book" year="1995">Harley 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rapini, A. &amp; Ribeiro, P. L. &amp; Lambert, S. &amp; Pirani, J. R." box="[638,852,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" pagination="16 - 24" refId="ref3645" refString="Rapini, A., Ribeiro, P. L., Lambert, S. &amp; Pirani, J. R. (2008) A flora dos campos rupestres da Cadeia do Espinhac ¸ o. Megadiversidade 4: 16 - 24." type="journal article" year="2008">
Rapini 
<emphasis box="[723,782,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Flowering from April to September. Fruiting from August to September.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5151440" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5151440" box="[136,1266,1416,1438]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5151440/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" startId="4.[136,229,1416,1438]" targetBox="[175,1424,400,1345]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1266,1416,1438]" box="[136,1266,1416,1438]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,247,1416,1438]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">FIGURE 3</emphasis>
. Map of the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[513,778,1416,1437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis box="[513,778,1416,1437]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(circles) and 
<taxonomicName box="[909,1165,1416,1437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urenifolium">
<emphasis box="[909,1165,1416,1437]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon urenifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(squares).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1484,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,441,1484,1510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—The first collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[739,1052,1484,1510]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis box="[739,1052,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded two years after the publication of a taxonomic revision of the Neotropical species of 
<taxonomicName box="[895,1057,1520,1546]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[895,1057,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, C. E." box="[1102,1298,1520,1546]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 313" refId="ref2845" refString="Anderson, C. E. (1997) Monograph of Stigmaphyllon (Malpighiaceae). Systematic Botany Monographs 51: 1 - 313. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 25027873" type="journal article" year="1997">Anderson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is represented by only a few records restricted to three municipalities within approximately 
<quantity box="[1180,1252,1556,1582]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" unit="km" value="90.0">90 km</quantity>
of each other, all of them with anthropomorphically modified Caatinga vegetation. Thus, according to IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (2012), this species should be regarded as Critically Endangered (categories B1a and B1b), due to its range of distribution being less than 
<quantity box="[446,531,1664,1690]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[530,538,1664,1678]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">2</superScript>
and continually declining habitat quality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1273,1700,1727]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1484,1979]" box="[189,1273,1700,1727]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1700,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to its restricted distribution within Caatinga vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1484,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,325,1736,1762]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Discussion:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[353,660,1736,1762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis box="[353,660,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive leafless species when flowering, a character only known for 
<taxonomicName authority="Diels (1937: 101)" authorityName="Diels" authorityPageNumber="101" authorityYear="1937" box="[177,681,1772,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudiflorum">
<emphasis box="[177,471,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon nudiflorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Diels, F. L. E." box="[480,681,1772,1798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" pagination="101" refId="ref3046" refString="Diels, F. L. E. (1937) Bibliotheca Botanica 29 (116): 101." type="journal article" year="1937">Diels (1937: 101)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[752,847,1772,1798]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and few other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1025,1190,1772,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malpighiaceae</taxonomicName>
species as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Griseb.) W. R. Anderson &amp; C. C. Davis (2006: 10)" authorityName="W. R. Anderson &amp; C. C. Davis" authorityPageNumber="10" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Griseb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Diplopterys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Diplopterys lutea</emphasis>
(Griseb.) W.R.Anderson &amp; C.C.Davis (2006: 10)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Griseb.) Nied. (1928: 336)" authorityName="Nied." authorityPageNumber="336" authorityYear="1928" baseAuthorityName="Griseb." box="[813,1412,1808,1835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Heteropterys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dumetorum">
<emphasis box="[813,1094,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Heteropterys dumetorum</emphasis>
(Griseb.) Nied. (1928: 336)
</taxonomicName>
. Its leaves are membranaceous, densely tomentose abaxially when young, and seem to grow right after fruit maturing. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,446,1880,1906]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis box="[136,446,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be mistakenly misidentified as a Cerrado species, 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Juss. (1833: 52)" authorityName="A. Juss." authorityPageNumber="52" authorityYear="1833" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urenifolium">
<emphasis box="[1065,1365,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon urenifolium</emphasis>
A.Juss. (1833: 52)
</taxonomicName>
, which also occurs within State of Bahia, and States of Minas Gerais and Mato Grosso do Sul. These species differ from each other mostly on leaf, gynoecium and fruit morphology (
<tableCitation box="[949,1032,1952,1978]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,158,182]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of diagnostic morphological characters between S. caatingicola and S. urenifolium." pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
